<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-125-004 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 826 176</DOCID><JOURNAL>Forbes  June 24 1991 v147 n13 p110(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Bobo Wang's midlife crisis. (president of Microtek InternationalInc.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Tanzer, Andrew.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Microtek International Inc, with estimated 1991 sales of $100million, is one of the leading companies in the image scannerindustry.andP;  The company was founded in the early 1980s by fiveUS-educated Taiwanese businessmen, including Pres Bobo Wang.andP;  Itcurrently has a market capitalization of $450 million, or 40 times1990 earnings.andP;  Microtek's first successful product was a circuitemulator, a tool used by electronics engineers to design and debugnew products; Microtek's was both smaller and less expensive thanthe leading emulators, made by HP and Intel Corp. Microtekfollowed its success with a low-priced black and white imagescanner that became the market leader.andP;  As the scanner marketopened up to more competition, Microtek astounded the othercompanies with a $2,695 color scanner.andP;  Microtek currentlydominates the color market, although HP leads the grayscalescanner business.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microtek International Inc. (Officials and employees).andO;Topic:     ManufacturersExecutiveManagement StyleScanning DevicesMarket Penetration.andO;Feature:   illustrationportrait.andO;Caption:   Bobo Wang. (portrait)Person:    Wang, Bobo (Management).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>